	at shaped history. Margaret Chase Smith stood alone on the Senate floor\, 
	summoning the courage to speak the truth. As McCarthyism gripped the natio
	n\, she issued her Declaration of Conscience—defying fear\, rejecting sile
	nce\, and holding her party publicly accountable. Though her stand came at
	 a personal cost\, her voice changed history forever. This powerful and qu
	ietly electrifying story still resonates today.\n\nhttps://web.ovationtix.
